<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-09-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="444" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Morrill</persName>,
                                    United States commissioner, to Mr. <persName type="to">Hoar</persName>, Attorney-General</hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Macon,
                                    Georgia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-09-06"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 6,
                                    1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Attorney-General United
                                    States</hi>:</p>
                            <p>Colonel Milledge, with Deputy Marshals Watson and Cox with <hi rend="italic">posse comitatus</hi>, left for Fort Gaines this
                                morning. Report that filibusters could not get over shoals in
                                river.</p>
                            <p><seg type="margin">[116]</seg> *Have forwarded your telegrams.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>W. C. MORRILL,<lb/><hi rend="italic">United States
                                        Commissioner.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>